qas.question: Who is the North Carolina state capital named for?
Who granted the charter for Sir Walter Raleigh to travel to present day North Carolina?
What year did Elizabeth I grant the charter to Raleigh to travel to North Carolina?
What was the second american territory the English attempted to colonize?
How many colonies did Raleigh establish on the coast of carolina in 1580?

context: In <a2_0>1584<a2_0/>, <a1_0>Elizabeth I<a1_0/> granted a charter to <a0_0>Sir Walter Raleigh<a0_0/>, for whom the state capital is named, for land in present-day <a3_0>North Carolina<a3_0/> (then part of the territory of Virginia). It was the second American territory which the English attempted to colonize. Raleigh established <a4_0>two<a4_0/> colonies on the coast in the late 1580s, but both failed. The fate of the "Lost Colony" of Roanoke Island remains one of the most widely debated mysteries of American history. Virginia Dare, the first English child to be born in North America, was born on Roanoke Island on August 18, 1587; Dare County is named for her.
